300
00:14:04,672 --> 00:14:07,138
And I thought, okay,
chief dying, right, you know,

301
00:14:07,138 --> 00:14:09,529
look up at the stars again,
look at the campfire.

302
00:14:09,529 --> 00:14:13,399
Chief die. What on Earth does
chief die have to do with the fence?

303
00:14:13,399 --> 00:14:16,416
"Chief die.

304
00:14:16,416 --> 00:14:18,854
First we destroy, yeah?
Then we reflect.

305
00:14:18,854 --> 00:14:22,708
Then we rebuild. Then we respect."

306
00:14:22,708 --> 00:14:26,656
And I burst out in tears, because
my father had only just died

307
00:14:26,656 --> 00:14:28,490
prior to this journey,

308
00:14:28,490 --> 00:14:30,161
and I didn't ever acknowledge him,

309
00:14:30,161 --> 00:14:34,120
I didn't ever appreciate him for the fact
that I'm probably standing here today

310
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:36,233
because of him.

311
00:14:36,233 --> 00:14:41,259
These people taught me that we are only
who we are because of our parents

312
00:14:41,259 --> 00:14:43,535
and our grandparents
and our forefathers

313
00:14:43,535 --> 00:14:45,346
going on and on and on before that,

314
00:14:45,346 --> 00:14:49,432
and I, no matter how romantic
or how idealistic I am on this journey,

315
00:14:49,432 --> 00:14:51,789
I did not know that until two weeks ago.

316
00:14:51,789 --> 00:14:54,738
I did not know that until two weeks ago.

